{"questionId":"25534","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A function, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>, has its derivative given by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>′</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>p</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>. The following&nbsp;diagram shows part of the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>′</mo></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/1100b7dade0b754c0f83bcdb3258dba9d472ee7a.png\"></p>\n<p>The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>′</mo></math> has an axis of symmetry <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The vertex of the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>′</mo></math> lies on the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence or otherwise, find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to substitute into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25534","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ1.7b.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence or otherwise, find the value of p.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Quadratic function"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}